Deleted User 2022-12-30 2:09 AM
Fill in the blank stories! You add random adjectives, verbs, nouns, etc. without knowing the context of the story. Each person takes a turn adding words. Then, at the end, you read the completed story (usually with hilarious results)

OOPS! Studio! 2023-04-28 11:25 AM
I have an old (maybe like.... 5 years?) SteelSeries controller that is really really bad! xd The triggers are so terrible to the point where I can't even use it. Holding down a trigger causes it to randomly switch on and off every couple seconds, or it will just not register at all.
11:25 AM
It's been like that since I bought it. It never got damaged or anything, it's just a common problem with that controller. I searched on the web and a ton of other people said the same thing happens, and sadly the DIY fix for it is very elaborate and risks breaking the whole thing so I can't fix it :(
11:26 AM
So just be weary of that if you go for a controller with gradual (%-based rather than binary) triggers.
